    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candle flickers its last, much like the light in my soul. He is gone, and with him, the very reason the sun dares to rise. It feels as though the fog of this London night is creeping into my very chest, slowing my heart, whispering that there is no point in fighting the tide anymore. I am so weary... I feel as though I am merely a ghost waiting for my body to realize it is already dead.",
