    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "But the choice feels so hollow. What warmth could there possibly be left? Every memory is just a thorn, and every tomorrow is just a heavier burden to carry. Even the stars look cold... indifferent to the fact that I am nothing. It would be so much quieter, wouldn't it? Just to let the silence finally take hold and be done with all this noise.",
